@startuml Calculator Class Diagram

title Calculator Class Diagram

class Calculator {
    +add(a, b)
    +subtract(a, b)
    +multiply(a, b)
    +divide(a, b)
    +factorial(n: int): int
    +square(x: float): float
    +cube(x: float): float
    +square_root(x: float): float
    +cube_root(x: float): float
    +log10(x: float): float
    +ln(x: float): float
    +power(x: float, y: float): float
}

class History {
    -_operations: list[str]
    +add_operation(operation_name: str, operands: list, result: float | int): None
    +get_all(): list[str]
    +save_to_file(filepath: str): None
    -_format_entry(operation_name: str, operands: list, result: float | int): str
}

note top of History
    Module: src/session/history.py
    Session-scoped operation tracker.
    Formats entries as operation(arg1, arg2, ...) = result.
    Persists to file on session end.
end note

class Logger {
    -_logger: logging.Logger
    +__init__(log_file: str = "error.log")
    +log_unsupported_operation(operation: str): None
    +log_invalid_operand(raw_value: str, expected_type: str): None
    +log_invalid_argument_count(operation: str, expected: int, given: int): None
    +log_division_by_zero(operands: list): None
    +log_domain_error(operation: str, error_message: str): None
}

note top of Logger
    Module: src/shared/logger.py
    Centralized file-based error logger.
    Appends plain-text lines to error.log.
    WARNING level: unsupported operations.
    ERROR level: coercion, arity, domain, divide-by-zero.
end note

note as OPERATIONS_NOTE
    <b>OPERATIONS</b> : dict[str, dict]
    Composed in src/operations/__init__.py
    from NORMAL_OPERATIONS (src/operations/normal.py)
    and SCIENTIFIC_OPERATIONS (src/operations/scientific.py).
    Maps operation keys to dispatch metadata:
    add, subtract, multiply, divide, power (arity=2)
    factorial (arity=1, coerce=int)
    square, cube, square_root, cube_root,
    log10, ln (arity=1, coerce=float)
    Each entry: { method, arity, label [, coerce] }
    Imported by session/input_handler.py and interface/cli.py.
end note

class OperationDispatcher {
    -_calculator: Calculator
    +__init__(calculator: Calculator)
    +coerce_operands(raw_args: list[str], coerce: Callable): list
    +dispatch(op_key: str, operands: list): float | int
}

note top of OperationDispatcher
    Module: src/shared/dispatcher.py
    Centralises operand coercion and method dispatch.
    Used by both InputHandler and CliDispatcher.
    No I/O or Logger dependency — callers handle errors.
end note

class InputHandler {
    -_calculator: Calculator
    -_input_fn: Callable[[str], str]
    -_history: History
    -_logger: Logger | None
    -_dispatcher: OperationDispatcher
    +__init__(calculator: Calculator, input_fn: Callable | None, logger: Logger | None)
    +run(): None
    -_show_menu(): None
    -_prompt_operands(arity: int, coerce: Callable): list
    -_dispatch(op_key: str, operands: list): float | int
}

note top of InputHandler
    Module: src/session/input_handler.py
    (shim: src/input_handler.py for backwards compat)
    Drives an interactive calculator REPL session.
    Re-exports OPERATIONS for backwards compatibility.
end note

note as RUN_SESSION_NOTE
    <b>run_session</b>(calculator: Calculator, input_fn: Callable | None, logger: Logger | None): None
    Free function in src/session/input_handler.py
    Convenience entry point: creates an InputHandler
    and calls handler.run()
end note

class CliDispatcher {
    -_calculator: Calculator
    -_logger: Logger | None
    -_dispatcher: OperationDispatcher
    +__init__(calculator: Calculator, logger: Logger | None)
    +dispatch_from_args(args: list[str]): int
    -_coerce_operands(raw_args: list[str], coerce: Callable): list
    -_dispatch(op_key: str, operands: list): float | int
    -_print_error(message: str): None
}

note top of CliDispatcher
    Module: src/interface/cli.py
    Parses CLI args, validates operands,
    dispatches to Calculator, prints result
    to stdout or error to stderr.
    Returns 0 on success, 1 on error.
end note

note as MAIN_NOTE
    <b>main()</b>
    Root-level entry point in main.py
    Creates Calculator + CliDispatcher,
    calls dispatch_from_args(sys.argv[1:]),
    exits with the returned code.
end note

OperationDispatcher --> Calculator : delegates calls to\n_calculator

InputHandler --> Calculator : holds reference via\n_calculator
InputHandler --> History : manages session history
InputHandler --> Logger : logs errors via\n_logger
InputHandler *-- OperationDispatcher : owns _dispatcher
InputHandler ..> OPERATIONS_NOTE : reads registry for\nmenu and dispatch
RUN_SESSION_NOTE ..> InputHandler : creates and calls run()

CliDispatcher --> Calculator : holds reference via\n_calculator
CliDispatcher --> Logger : logs errors via\n_logger
CliDispatcher *-- OperationDispatcher : owns _dispatcher
CliDispatcher ..> OPERATIONS_NOTE : reads registry for\narity and coerce
MAIN_NOTE ..> CliDispatcher : creates and calls\ndispatch_from_args()

@enduml
